      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERSPIRATION (3) won at a price at Hobart over 1200m despite just missing here prior. He's still well shy of his best Sydney form and looks to be hitting his straps for John Key. Has won 2/3 over 1400m, and Luke Currie will give him every chance. Left the one to beat. IN THE OCEAN (5) continues to race well without winning. Has been kept on the fresh side and tumbles in weight today. That brings him right into it. GEEGEES GEMSTONE (1) has been knocking on the door and may be looking for the longer sprint. Can't be ruled out. TURK WARRIOR (2) has needed racing for the new stable but goes third-up and has placed in a Devonport trial since his last run a month ago. We are likely to see a better effort.",
